The paper focuses on studying human behavior and social interactions on Instagram, which is a social media platform. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also analyzes the structural characteristics of the network, content production and consumption, and user behavior in labeling media with tags, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Development), cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks), and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper aims to understand how collective trends emerge from individuals' topical interests, which could be related to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
